metadata.name: The Ocean Waves #34
metadata.description:
Ocean waves in calm or stormy skies. Spray, and the occasional buoy passes by.

Large and rolling waves are generated at the back and get more turbulent as they get closer to the viewer. A stripe of sunlight varies in position from towards the back to the front. The highest waves create spray. Everyone once and a while, a buoy or two (or more!) will pass by. The background color is related to the buoy color to make it more harmonious.

metadata.name: fx(mandala) #108
metadata.description:
Outer mandalas represent the universe or world-system and are traditionally offered as thank you gifts. In this case it’s my offering to the fxhash community as a celebration of #fxhashturnsone. 

SOME MINTS WILL BE GOLDEN TICKETS
A golden ticket AND the iteration directly before it will each receive a free 8 x 10in special edition signed physical made from 12 layers of laser cut museum board. 

Physicals for all mints can be requested and/or claimed at https://alleditions.art

Outer Mandalas is part of a broader series I am working on that explores the use of techniques and patterns from sacred geometries using generative randomness. I use generative algorithms to create “blueprints” that can be transferred out of the physical realm and into the real world as multi-layered three dimensional sculptures. 

I create limited edition physical “prints” for Outer Mandalas by using a high powered laser to precisely cut through 4-ply museum boards (the same stuff you frame a picture with) to create 12 unique layers. I then stack and carefully glue each layer together in order to create a dynamic relief that plays with light and shadow. These pieces are visually engaging artworks that tend to spark conversation whenever they are seen.  

A big thank you to the fxhash platform team and all the passionate collectors and generative artists I’ve met over the past year. It’s been my honor to be a part of this amazing community. 

s to save as a layered SVG 
p to save as a PNG
e to explode the layers
Click and drag the mouse to change the shadows. 

This generative is VERY intensive and probably won’t render very well on a mobile device.

metadata.name: zdiak-grphk #364
metadata.description:
fxhash turns one

Working with text on GEN XYZ Das Occult led me to fooling around with an ascii type project while I worked on those pfps. Gradually that project morphed into this strange hybrid of indie posters, zodiac killer messages and what AI might do to the whole thing. If it were unleashed on it. This collection - I prefer to call my art a collection - includes some palettes inspired by influential fxhash projects as well as mixes of my own.

Themes here can be pretty dark. I've struggled with suicidal ideation in the past and while it seems like it might be a faux pas to put the words suicide and death in these works, I felt I needed to stay true to me and the darkness that tends to walk side by side with the sunny man I often appear to be.

If you struggle with similar issues, please go and speak to someone. It has helped me immensely.

fxhash asked everyone to try and make some donations to worthy causes.

I chose Processing Foundation - since their code work has been so helpful to this community. And to Tezos Ukraine. Because the war there goes beyond the borders of Ukraine and the outcome will have an impact on our global society. If Putin were to succeed... Well he won't with our help.

metadata.name: The muon in the hole #173
metadata.description:
Special collection for #fxhashturnsone.

Halftones, dynamic composition and contrasts.

Procedural realtime javascript / webgl.
Desktop / Chrome recommended.


Controls :
- Mouse wheel/middle/ Pinch : Zoom
- After zooming, Mouse left / Drag : Pan
- Press [r] to reset the camera.
- Press [f] to toggle the frame.
- Press [c] to fully unlock the camera, with rotation on Mouse2.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys [1] to [9] (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels for the smallest dimension. I recommend starting with [4] and going from there. What is captured is what's on screen, so you can get creative if you so desire.

NFT License

metadata.description:
An undulating (sometimes) landscape made up of hexagons (or "Hexagones" laying in wait) to celebrate the first birthday of fxhash. Written at the last minute the weekend before the birthday week.

A simpler 16 colour version of this project was originally coded on an Atari ST 512, about 32 years ago, figured it was time to update it.

s - Download and save image

metadata.name: Rite of Passage #184
metadata.description:
In life, we all take different paths, different rites of passage, and while the end is all that's ever true, we will still all view it and experience it in very different ways, like that masterpiece hanging on the wall at the end of our gallery visit. 
  

There are always things that we will never have the power to change, but at the same time, we determine the route, we influence the journey, we can choose the person we want to be. We'll look back on memories, we'll have regrets, and we'll think about what could have been - but unlike this artwork, in the end we won't be able to change the final output by simply pressing a number - so live well and be happy my friends. 

---------------------

metadata.name: [fxhashturnsone] 2022 A Generative Odyssey #118
metadata.description:
🪐🌌✨

2022 A Generative Odyssey (Story of a traveler)

A simple space landscape generator 🏞
Allows some exploration for curious ones 📡
Don't forget to press "4" to take a panoramic picture 📸🤳

🕳🧭🛰



-----
* Technics *

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Pure code / no external assets
- Interactive / orbitable
- 8 scenes with unlimited possible variations
- 5 capture / screenshot modes 8K+

-----
* Controls *

Left click / touch + drag : orbit around center of interest
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

Keyboard "1" : PNG capture the current view at same resolution / ratio 
Keyboard "2" : PNG capture view as square 4320x4320
Keyboard "3" : PNG capture at best resolution 8K (7680x4320)
Keyboard "4" : PNG capture as panoramic view (8192x2304)
Keyboard "5" : PNG capture as super-panoramic (10650x3000)

-----
* URL modifier *

"&r=1"
enables auto rotation of view (equivalent to "R" key press)

-----
* Mint details *

- Mint preview / capture is PNG 1920x1920

-----
@HAL09999 – May/November 2022
